\section{Methodology}


\subsection{Heston Model}

The Heston model prices European options using the characteristic function method with Black-Scholes pricing as the baseline. Parameters calibrated:

\begin{equation}
\Theta = \{\nu_0, \theta, \rho, \kappa, \sigma\}
\end{equation}

where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item $\nu_0$ = Initial instantaneous variance (annualized)
    \item $\theta$ = Long-run mean variance
    \item $\rho$ = Correlation between spot and volatility
    \item $\kappa$ = Mean reversion speed
    \item $\sigma$ = Volatility of volatility
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Calibration Approach}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Optimization}: L-BFGS-B (Limited-memory Broyden-Fletcher-Goldfarb-Shanno with box constraints) with 5,000 iterations
    \item \textbf{Cross-Validation}: 5-fold stratified split on moneyness
    \item \textbf{Constraints}: Feller condition enforced ($2\kappa\theta \geq \sigma^2$)
    \item \textbf{Error Metrics}: RMSE, MAE (Mean Absolute Error), relative percentage errors, and parameter stability
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Performance Metrics}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{In-Sample}: Fit quality on the calibration dataset
    \item \textbf{Out-of-Sample (OOS)}: Predictive performance on held-out test folds
    \item \textbf{Generalization Gap}: OOS metric minus in-sample metric (negative = good, indicates no overfitting)
    \item \textbf{Parameter Std Dev}: Standard deviation of calibrated parameters across folds (lower = more stable)
\end{itemize}


